The paper deals with deep neural networks for predicting both semantic labels and salient objects in images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques for dual task prediction, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The analysis of object co-occurrences also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. Finally, the paper deals with image processing and analysis, which is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
